# FortuneSheet fork — upstream compatibility

Canonical consumer: **`vendor/*.tgz`**, branch **`dhsl/v1.0.4`**, details in **`docs/DECISIONS.md`**. Complements **`.cursor/rules/patch-templates.mdc`** (product/template rules).

## Git workflow (fork clone)

- Add remote **`upstream`** → `https://github.com/ruilisi/fortune-sheet.git` (or `git@github.com:ruilisi/fortune-sheet.git`).
- **Base branch** should match the **npm version** this app pins (e.g. tag **`v1.0.4`**). Do not mix upstream `main` onto a branch meant to track **`v1.0.4`** without a deliberate version bump in **this** repo.
- **One commit per logical fix** (touch pan, getSheetIndex, applyOp guard, …). Message: imperative, **why** + **symptom** (helps upstream PR and cherry-pick).
- **Push after commit:** On **`doug86i/fortune-sheet`**, after **`git commit`** on **`dhsl/v1.0.4`**, run **`git push origin dhsl/v1.0.4`** before finishing the agent task that also updates **`vendor/*.tgz`** in **this** repo (when network and credentials allow). Fork history on GitHub must not lag a local-only commit.
- **No drive-by changes:** no mass Prettier on unrelated files, no dependency bumps unrelated to the fix, no generated **`dist/`** committed in the fork repo (build only for **`npm pack`**).

## Source boundaries

- Prefer edits under **`packages/core/src/`** and **`packages/react/src/`** only. Avoid changing **`packages/formula-parser`** unless the fix truly belongs there.
- After edits: **`yarn install`** (if needed), **`npm run build`** at repo root, then **`npm pack`** in **`packages/core/`** and **`packages/react/`**. (**`git commit`** / **`git push`** follow the **Git workflow** bullets above.)

## Merging upstream later

1. **`git fetch upstream`**
2. Merge or rebase **`upstream/main`** (or the relevant release branch/tag) onto **`dhsl/v1.0.4`**, or create **`dhsl/v1.0.5`** from new upstream tag and **cherry-pick** DHSL commits.
3. Resolve conflicts **in TypeScript source**, rebuild, run a quick smoke (build succeeds).
4. In **this** repo: copy new **`.tgz`** to **`vendor/`**, refresh **`package-lock.json`** integrity (`npm install` with the **`file:./vendor/...`** pattern — see **`AGENTS.md`** § *FortuneSheet fork — updating tarballs*).
5. Update **`docs/DECISIONS.md`**: drop bullets for commits that landed upstream; note new fork-only commits.

## Upstream-first

- Open **PRs to `ruilisi/fortune-sheet`** when the change is generally useful; keep fork commit messages aligned with PR description.
- If upstream merges a fix, **revert or drop** the matching commit on **`dhsl/*`** on next merge to reduce drift.

## This repo (`changeoverlord`)

- Never hand-edit **`node_modules/@fortune-sheet/*`**. Never **`patch-package`** FortuneSheet (see **patch-templates** rule).
- Tarball updates and lockfile integrity belong in the **same commit** as the behavioural change when practical.
